\c 11
\s1 Makanan yang haram dan tidak haram.
\p
\v 1 TUHAN berkata kepada Harun dan Musa,
\v 2 "Katakan kepada orang-orang Israel bahwa ​​dari semua binatang yang hidup di darat, inilah yang diizinkan TUHAN untuk di makan:
\v 3 Binatang yang memiliki kuku yang benar-benar terbelah dan hewan yang memamah biak.
\p
\v 4 Ada beberapa hewan yang memamah biak tapi tidak memiliki kuku yang terbelah, dan ada beberapa binatang yang memiliki kuku terbelah tapi tidak memamah biak. Kalian tidak boleh memakan hewan-hewan itu,contohnya: unta memang memamah biak tapi tidak memiliki kuku yang terbelah, jadi itu haram bagimu.
\v 5 Pelanduk memang memamah biak tapi tidak memiliki kuku yang terbelah, jadi itu juga haram bagimu.
\v 6 Kelinci memamah biak tapi tidak memiliki kuku yang terbelah, jadibinatang ini juga haram bagimu.
\v 7 Babi benar-benar berkuku belah tapi mereka tidak memamah biak, jadi itu haram bagimu.
\v 8 Semua hewan tersebut haram, jadi kalian tidak boleh makan dagingnya bahkan menyentuh bangkainyapun tidak boleh.
\p
\v 9 Dari semua makhluk yang hidup di lautan dan sungai, Kalian boleh makan apapun yang memiliki sirip dan sisik.
\v 10 Tapi kalian tidak boleh makan yang tidak memiliki sirip dan tidak memiliki sisik. Itu termasuk yang menjijikkan bagimu.
\v 11 Binatang itu merupakan makanan yang menjijikkan bagimu, dan kalian tidak boleh memakan dagingnya, dan kalian harus jijik terhadap bangkainya.
\v 12 Segala sesuatu yang hidup di air yang tidak memiliki sirip dan tidak memiliki sisik. merupakan makanan yang menjijikkan bagimu.
\p
\v 13 Ada beberapa burung yang tidak boleh kalian makan yaitu: burung elang, burung pemangsa berjanggut, burung nasar hitam,
\v 14 burung layang-layang, jenis-jenis elang,
\v 15 semua jenis gagak,
\v 16 burung hantu bertanduk, burung unta, burung camar, dan semua jenis elang,
\v 17 burung pungguk, burung dendang air, burung hantu besar,
\v 18 burung hantu putih, burung hantu padang pasir, burung nazar,
\v 19bangau, jenis bangau, kelopak, dan kelelawar.
\p
\v 20 You must detest \add and not eat\add* flying insects that \add sometimes\add* walk on the ground [MTY].
\v 21 But you are permitted to eat creatures with wings that sometimes walk on the ground if they have jointed legs for hopping around.
\v 22 They include locusts, crickets, and grasshoppers.
\v 23 But you must detest \add and not eat\add* other insects with wings that have four legs.
\p
\v 24 There are certain creatures that if you touch their carcasses you will become defiled. Anyone who touches their carcasses must not touch other people until that evening.
\v 25 Anyone who picks up one of their carcasses must wash his clothes and not touch other people until that evening.
\p
\v 26 The animals whose carcasses you must not touch are those that have hooves that are not completely divided or animals that do not chew their cuds. Anyone who touches the carcasses of any of those animals becomes ◄defiled/unacceptable to me►.
\v 27 From all the animals that walk on the ground, you must not touch the carcasses of those that have paws to walk on. Anyone who touches one of their carcasses must not touch other people until that evening.
\v 28 Anyone who picks up one of their carcasses must wash his clothes and not touch other people until that evening, because iouching their carcasses ◄defiles you/causes you to become unacceptable to me►.
\p
\v 29 From all the animals that walk on the ground, these are the ones that ◄defile you/cause you to become unacceptable to me►\add if you touch them\add*: Moles, rats, any kind of lizard,
\v 30 geckos, skinks, and chameleons.
\v 31 Those creatures that crawl along the ground ◄defile you/cause you to become unacceptable to me►; anyone who touches one of their carcasses must not touch other people until the evening.
\v 32 When one of those creatures dies and falls on something, the thing that it falls on, whatever it is used for, will become ◄defiled/unacceptable to me►, whether it is made of wood or cloth or the hide of some animal or from rough cloth. You must put it in water. Then you must not use it until that evening.
\v 33 If one of them falls into a clay pot, everything in it becomes defiled, and you must break that pot.
\v 34 If you pour water from that pot on any food, you must not eat that food. And you must not drink any water from that pot.
\v 35 Anything that one of the carcasses of those creatures falls on becomes ◄defiled/unacceptable to me►; even if it falls on an oven or a cooking pot, anything that it falls on must be broken. It becomes unacceptable to me and you must not use it again.
\v 36 If one of their carcasses falls into a spring or a pit for storing water, the water may still be drunk, but anyone who touches one of those carcasses becomes unacceptableto me.
\v 37 If one of those carcasses falls on seeds that are to be planted, those seeds are still acceptable to be planted.
\v 38 But if water has been put on the seeds and then a carcass falls on them, the seeds must be thrown away.
\p
\v 39 If an animal \add whose meat\add* you are permitted to eat dies, anyone who touches its carcass must not touch other people until that evening.
\v 40 Anyone who eats some meat from that carcass must wash his clothes, and then he must not touch anyone until that evening.
\p
\v 41-42 All creatures that crawl along the ground, including those that move on their bellies and those that crawl, are detestable, and they must not be eaten.
\v 43 Do not ◄defile yourselves/cause you to become unacceptable to me► by\add eating\add* any of those creatures [DOU].
\v 44 I am Yahweh your God, and I am holy, so you must consecrate yourselves and be holy. You must avoid eating things that cause you to beunaceoptable to me. Do not cause yourselves to become unacceptable to me by eating creatures that crawl along on the ground.
\v 45 I am Yahweh, their one who \add freed you from being slaves\add* in Egypt, in order to be your God. Therefore, because I am holy, you must be holy.
\p
\v 46 Those are the regulations concerning animals and birds, all the living creatures that live in water or scurry along on the ground.
\v 47 You must learn what things \add I say\add* are acceptable to me and what things are not, and learn what things you are permitted to eat and what things you are not permitted to eat.”